                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.00 Revolutions/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-03T09:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 3, 1931—9 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">p.m.</hi>]</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:26 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. My 101, December 3, 7 p.m. President reached Santa Ana at 7:30 and the Army
                    Commander gave him command of the town. I believe nevertheless his chances are
                    hopeless.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
